+# Real Estate Backend + Frontend Deployment Guide
+
+This project is now configured for **single-service deployment** (Express serves the built Vite app in production).
+
+## 1) Required environment variables
+
+Create these variables in your hosting provider:
+
+- `MONGODB_URL` - MongoDB connection string
+- `JWT_SECRET` - JWT signing secret used by auth controllers
+- `CLIENT_URL` - Public frontend URL (used for CORS), for example `https://your-app.onrender.com`
+- `NODE_ENV` - set to `production`
+
+For local development, keep using your local `.env` file.
+
+## 2) Deploy on Render (recommended for this setup)
+
+1. Push this repository to GitHub.
+2. In Render, create a **Web Service** connected to this repo.
+3. Configure:
+   - **Build Command:** `npm install && npm run build`
+   - **Start Command:** `npm start`
+4. Add the environment variables above.
+5. Deploy.
+
+Render will:
+- install backend dependencies,
+- build the frontend into `frontend/dist`,
+- run `node backend/index.js`,
+- and Express will serve both API (`/api/*`) and frontend routes.
+
+## 3) Local production smoke test (optional)
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm run build
+NODE_ENV=production npm start
+```
+
+Open `http://localhost:3000` for the frontend and `http://localhost:3000/api/health` for backend health.
+
+## 4) Development workflow
+
+Run backend dev server from repo root:
+
+```bash
+npm run dev
+```
+
+Run frontend separately in another terminal:
+
+```bash
+cd frontend
+npm install
+npm run dev
+```
+
+Frontend dev server proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:3000` via Vite config.
